contentrichtext.text: '''[[Denmark]]''' is a country located principally in Northern Europe. Denmark may also refer to: {{TOC right}} == Political entities == * [[Denmark (European Parliament constituency)]], the associated constituency * The Kingdom of Denmark, consisting of Denmark, [[Greenland]] and the [[Faroe Islands]] == Municipalities, communities, streets == In '''Australia''': * [[Denmark, Western Australia]] In the '''United Kingdom''' *[[Denmark Street]], London street In the '''United States''': * [[Denmark, Iowa]] * [[Denmark, Maine]] * [[Denmark, New York]] * [[Denmark, South Carolina]] * [[Denmark, Wisconsin]] == Geographic landforms == * [[Denmark Bay]], Nunavut, Canada * [[Denmark Island]], in [[Scoresby Sund]], on the east coast of Greenland * [[Denmark Sound]] (Danmark fjord), on the northeast tip of Greenland * [[Denmark Strait]], between Iceland and Greenland * [[Denmark River]], in Western Australia == People == * [[House of Denmark]] * [[Erik Denmark]], American competitive eater * Dr. [[Leila Denmark]], American pediatrician * [[Rob Denmark]], British middle- and long distance runner * [[Denmark Vesey]] (1767?-1822), North American slave (later freedman) and instigator of a slave revolt == Entertainment == * [[Denmark (film)|''Denmark'' (film)]], a 2010 short film * "Denmark", a song by The Chemical Brothers on their album ''[[Come with Us]]'' * Denmark, the fictional personification of the country the manga ''[[Hetalia: Axis Powers]]'' by Hidekaz Himaruya == See also == * [[Danmark (armoured frigate)|''Danmark'' (armoured frigate)]], a Danish warship (1864–1900) * [[Denmark Township (disambiguation)]] * [[New Denmark (disambiguation)]] * {{lookfrom|Denmark}} * {{intitle|Denmark}} {{disambig|geo|surname}}
